addLiquidity(uint256).details: Allows anyone to add liquidity to the market (must be running)

params.amount: Amount of collateral to add as liquidity

calcMarginalPrice(uint8).details: Returns marginal price of an outcome

params.outcomeTokenIndex: Index of outcome to determine marginal price of

returns.price: Marginal price of an outcome as a fixed point number

calcMarketFee(uint256).details: Calculates fee to be paid to market maker

calcNetCost(int256[]).details: Calculates the net cost for executing a given trade.

params.outcomeTokenAmounts: Amounts of outcome tokens to buy from the market. If an amount is negative, represents an amount to sell to the market.

returns.netCost: Net cost of trade. If positive, represents amount of collateral which would be paid to the market for the trade. If negative, represents amount of collateral which would be received from the market for the trade.

changeFunding(int256).details: Allows to fund the market with collateral tokens converting them into outcome tokens Note for the future: should combine splitPosition and mergePositions into one function, as code duplication causes things like this to happen.

close().details: Allows market owner to close the market (stops trading)

getPendingFees(address).details: Allows anyone to view their pending fee earnings

getSharePercentage(address).details: Get LP share percentage (in basis points, 10000 = 100%)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeemPositions().details: Redeems all outcome tokens back to collateral after oracle resolves the condition Can be called by anyone once the oracle has reported results Must be called before LPs can withdraw their liquidity

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

trade(int256[],int256).details: Allows to trade outcome tokens and collateral with the market maker

params.collateralLimit: If positive, this is the limit for the amount of collateral tokens which will be sent to the market to conduct the trade. If negative, this is the minimum amount of collateral tokens which will be received from the market for the trade. If zero, there is no limit.
params.outcomeTokenAmounts: Amounts of each atomic outcome token to buy or sell. If positive, will buy this amount of outcome token from the market. If negative, will sell this amount back to the market instead.

returns.netCost: If positive, the amount of collateral sent to the market. If negative, the amount of collateral received from the market. If zero, no collateral was sent or received.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawFees().details: Allows liquidity providers to withdraw their share of accumulated fees

returns.userFees: Amount of fees withdrawn by caller

withdrawLiquidity().details: Allows LPs to withdraw their share of liquidity after market is closed and redeemed
